This paper discusses an extension to the tabling technique in Prolog, which is a programming language used in artificial intelligence and logic programming. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses optimizations to the table space organization, which relates to database systems (cs.DB) and logic (cs.LO). Finally, the paper discusses experimental results, which could also be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
